snippet.textDisplay: Personal opinion: The rapper ALY HASAN just ruined a well composed song. I think the track has lost a of meaning and credibility by the inclusion of his weak lyricism and it really does not add any layer to the track. We need to get out of this tendency of adding a rap verse from a local rapper in between tracks in almost every song. How many coke studio songs have been made in this pattern already! This is so 2016! Also, we need to stop including just anyone to the music videos just because he got big on social media.

snippet.textDisplay:
Now that I've had some time to process the song, here are my thoughts. 

The song is very addictive, a perfect juxtaposition of new and old, folk and rap. Everything looks fit together perfectly even though on paper it's not supposed to work.
The chorus in particular is extremely catchy. 

The lead singer, I'm guessing Sagor Dewan, was the perfect choice for his place. His voice is so clean that when the chaos of life takes over (in this case, all the intruments of the song) you can close your eyes and let yourself float in his voice like calm waves like the soothing feeling of nostalgia.

The rapper's attitude "ভাই, আপনিই গান" added a lovely playfulness to the song.

Life is short, yes our childhood nostalgia will forever be dear to us but it's important not to forget to have fun in the midst of the chaos that is our adult life.

Once again, the set design and costume are bangers.

Edit

It would be a great disservice not to credit the camera and direction of the music video. It's just phenomenal!
